  "prompt": "What steps would a person need to take to get hired by the World Bank or the IMF?",
  "response": "To get hired by the World Bank or the IMF, here are some typical steps:\n\n1. Educational Requirements\n- Advanced degree (Master's or PhD) in economics, international development, finance, public policy\n- Strong academic credentials from a reputable university\n- Language skills (French, Spanish, Arabic are often valuable)\n\n2. Professional Qualifications\n- Relevant work experience in development, economics, finance\n- Internships or research positions in international organizations\n- Strong analytical and research skills\n- Demonstrated understanding of global economic issues\n\n3. Application Process\n- Check job openings on official websites\n- Create an online profile\n- Submit detailed application with resume/CV\n- Complete online assessments\n- Pass initial screening\n\n4. Specific Skills\n- Technical expertise in economic modeling\n- Data analysis capabilities\n- Understanding of global economic trends\n- Policy analysis skills\n\n5. Networking\n- Attend development conferences\n- Connect with current employees\n- Participate in professional development programs\n- Follow organization's publications and research\n\n6. Additional Considerations\n- Most competitive candidates have international experience\n- Strong writing and communication skills\n- Ability to work in multicultural environments\n- Some positions require relocation to Washington D.C.\n\nCompetitive positions, typically requiring significant qualifications and experience.",
